      "id": "05a89c4c-dcb7-439b-9597-ffad0af1619d",
      "type": "markdown",
      "source": "Listing 7: An immutable \u0060Person\u0060 class. Attributes are set at\nconstruction time. State can only be updated via the creation of new\nobjects."
    },
    {
      "id": "cca5af96-0969-4a50-bdbf-b907b894df81",
      "type": "code",
      "language": "csharp",
      "source": "class Person {\n    private int _age;\n    public int Age { get =\u003E _age; }\n\n    private string _name;\n    public string Name { get =\u003E _name; }\n\n    public Person(string name, int age)\n    {\n        if (name.Length == 0)\n            throw new ArgumentOutOfRangeException(nameof(name),\n                                                  \u0022cannot be empty\u0022);\n        if (age \u003C 0)\n            throw new ArgumentOutOfRangeException(nameof(age),\n                                                  \u0022cannot be negative\u0022);\n        _name = name;\n        _age = age;\n    }\n}\n\nPerson SetAge(Person p, int age) {\n    if (age \u003C 0){\n        return p;\n    }\n    return new Person(p.Name, age);\n}\n\nvar p = new Person(\u0022Eleanor\u0022, 22);\nvar p2 = SetAge(p, 23);\nConsole.WriteLine($\u0022p.Age = {p.Age}\u0022)\nConsole.WriteLine($\u0022p2.Age = {p2.Age}\u0022)"
    },
    {
