      "id": "5654066e-5cfc-4c36-a5b4-b48314e656df",
      "type": "markdown",
      "source": "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nListing 14: The behaviour of Add depends not only on the values for a\nand b."
    },
    {
      "id": "d8c7ff18-d670-4306-b197-19acf1efc36a",
      "type": "code",
      "language": "csharp",
      "source": "int called = 0;\n\nint Add(int a, int b) {\n    int sum = a \u002B b;\n\n    sum \u002B= called;\n    \n    called\u002B\u002B; // change state\n\n    Console.WriteLine(\u0022Result is {0}.\u0022, sum); // perform I/O\n    return sum;\n}\n\nConsole.WriteLine(Add(1,2)); // 3\nConsole.WriteLine(Add(1,2)); // 4!"
    },
