    {
      "id": "843376bb-8d97-4869-bd50-b279daf95751",
      "type": "markdown",
      "source": "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n**Exercise 8** Determine for the functions in lsts.\u00A018-20, which are\npure and which are not. Motivate your answer.\n\nListing 18: The function randomNumber returns a number between 0 and max"
    },
    {
      "id": "17f20a69-0e5f-450c-88bf-e0e2262f6a84",
      "type": "code",
      "language": "csharp",
      "source": "let randomNumber max  =\n    let r = System.Random()\n    r.Next max"
    },
    {
      "id": "f076ba35-947b-4abe-9c96-52821d7ca819",
      "type": "markdown",
      "source": "Listing 19: This time we seed the random number generated with the same\nnumber"
